page.title: 13TEMPLE WOOD,K.UNDERWOOD cont
page.content: A varied and exciting selection of wildlife is found within Temple Wood, including Badgers and species of deer. An estimated seventy Fallow Deer and many Red Deer have been seen this year. In addition the small Muntjac Deer is evident. Whilst the Red Deer is protected and preserved, fourteen Fallow (mainly bucks) were culled last year. Birds are found in abundance; the many varieties of wild species, both resident and migratory and the local pheasants which are raised in large numbers in readiness for the shooting season. (Approximately 200 are shot each year.) A team of licenced bird ringers has ringed nearly 8000 birds of 56 species over the past 5 years, mainly Greenfinch and Chaffinch but including the rarer Woodcock,Hawfinch, Sparrow Hawk,Nightingale & Woodpeckers
